From: GSI Builder <gsi@example.com>
Date: Sun, 2 Mar 2026 19:45:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Remove HIDL audio HAL entries from bluetooth audio manifest

The bluetooth_audio_system.xml declared HIDL android.hardware.audio
@2.0 through @7.1 via hwbinder transport. On AIDL-only Vendor15
targets, these cause false service registrations and unnecessary
hwservicemanager probes that can stall boot.

Retains the AIDL bluetooth.audio v4 entry which is the correct
transport for A15+ vendors.

diff --git a/bluetooth/audio/hal/bluetooth_audio_system.xml b/bluetooth/audio/hal/bluetooth_audio_system.xml
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/bluetooth/audio/hal/bluetooth_audio_system.xml
+++ b/bluetooth/audio/hal/bluetooth_audio_system.xml
@@ -1,17 +1,8 @@
 <manifest version="1.0" type="framework">
     <hal format="aidl">
         <name>android.hardware.bluetooth.audio</name>
         <version>4</version>
         <fqname>IBluetoothAudioProviderFactory/sysbta</fqname>
     </hal>
-    <hal>
-        <name>android.hardware.audio</name>
-        <transport>hwbinder</transport>
-        <fqname>@2.0::IDevicesFactory/sysbta</fqname>
-        <fqname>@4.0::IDevicesFactory/sysbta</fqname>
-        <fqname>@5.0::IDevicesFactory/sysbta</fqname>
-        <fqname>@6.0::IDevicesFactory/sysbta</fqname>
-        <fqname>@7.0::IDevicesFactory/sysbta</fqname>
-        <fqname>@7.1::IDevicesFactory/sysbta</fqname>
-    </hal>
+    <!-- HIDL audio HAL entries removed: AIDL-only policy (Vendor15 GSI) -->
 </manifest>
